# Instagram Ad & Tracking Block List
# Format: standard hosts file (0.0.0.0 domain)
# Last updated: 2026-03-23
#
# Sources:
#   - Live DNS log analysis (AdAway DNS request export)
#   - NetSeer (ad-tech company acquired by Facebook) IP association tracker
#
# Usage:
#   AdAway → Hosts Sources → Add → paste the raw URL of this file
#   OR manually add each domain to your block list
#
# NOTE: Instagram serves ads through the same API endpoints as organic content.
#       DNS blocking cannot remove in-feed/story ads — only trackers can be blocked.
#       Domains marked [SKIP] are known to break the app if blocked.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Ad Targeting & IP Association (NetSeer / Facebook)
# NetSeer was an ad-tech company acquired by Facebook.
# These domains associate device IP addresses with user identifiers for ad targeting.
# NOTE: The GUID prefix (cbb3880e-...) may change per device/session.
#       Update these entries from your own AdAway DNS log export if they stop matching.
0.0.0.0 cbb3880e-3bf5-4ee5-8817-ca6ca2129c67-netseer-ipaddr-assoc.xy.fbcdn.net
0.0.0.0 cbb3880e-3bf5-4ee5-8817-ca6ca2129c67-netseer-ipaddr-assoc.xz.fbcdn.net

# ── DO NOT BLOCK (breaks the app) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# [SKIP] graph.instagram.com              — core API (feed, stories, reels)
# [SKIP] i.instagram.com                  — core API (login, profile, media)
# [SKIP] instagram.fsxv2-1.fna.fbcdn.net  — profile pictures, story thumbnails
# [SKIP] scontent.fsxv2-1.fna.fbcdn.net   — feed images and videos
# [SKIP] graph.facebook.com               — shared Facebook/Instagram API
# [SKIP] lookaside.facebook.com           — image CDN
# [SKIP] z-p42-chat-e2ee-ig.facebook.com  — Instagram E2E encrypted DMs
# [SKIP] z-m-gateway.facebook.com         — mobile gateway
# [SKIP] media2.giphy.com                 — GIFs in DMs
# [SKIP] media4.giphy.com                 — GIFs in DMs
